I’m thrilled to share this easy and fun sensory art activity that I’ve partnered with Johnson & Johnson to come up with! We love bath time painting, especially Abby as she can paint to her heart’s content. Simple to do with your little ones for more bonding time, it’s also so easy to clean up! Simply shower Abby and the walls at the same time. 

This amazing bath time paint can be created with four items you can easily find at home. We love using our Johnson’s®️ Milk + Rice Bath, because this gentle soap packed with milk proteins, rice extracts, multiple vitamins and minerals that keeps Abby’s skin all nourished even when she’s painting away with her hands. 

Johnson’s Baby is also running a giveaway on their Facebook page, so do head over for a chance to win an exclusive Johnson’s Baby activity pack (worth $100).

I think I just created my favorite shelf ever!

Zachary is obsessed with all things Star Wars right now and his obsession has definitely rubbed off on me. Honestly, it wasn’t easy pulling this shelf off with a newborn in the house. It took me more than a week of late nights but so worth it! Can you sense my excitement?! 😁😁 We are ready for May 4th! 
Watch the full video of the making of this #starwars shelf on my IGTV. 
Are you a Star Wars fan? Let’s chat in the comments below! 🤩

Here’s a fun bilateral coordination challenge for your children! The first challenge was for Riley to fly her rockets 🚀 through all the blue planets. The blue planet stood out the most from the rest of the colors so this was the easiest task. The second challenge was to fly her rockets through all the red planets. The red, orange and yellow planets look more similar, so it was more challenging for my 6yo to land her rockets on the red planets quickly. The last challenge was to fly the rockets to planets of a chosen numbers. Because the planets are all of the same colors, it was more challenging to differentiate the numbers. Children loved these challenges. We took turns with this challenge and timed each other. Have fun with this one! 😍

node.text:
Space Theme Learning Shelf 🚀🌎
We had a blast learning about the space theme at home this month! I was worried that the Space theme was going to be too abstract for 2yo Abby and she wouldn’t be interested in the activities. But guess what, she blew my mind! She willingly tried most of the activities and along the way, she picked up a thing or two about the space. Like she would happily fly her rocket around the house everyday and tell me that she’s going to the Moon. Or she would point out the Space station pictures in the Space books because we did a Space Station puzzle. So my reflection this month: Kids will learn what they want to learn/ when they are ready to learn! Through our monthly theme, my children get to explore a variety of topics, subjects and skills and they never fail to surprise me what they learnt through  along the way! That’s why I just love what I do, creating rich learning experiences and watch my children get curious and excited about learning. ❤️
. 
.

Today feels like a good day for an overdue intro post, so here goes! Hi to all my followers, new and old, I am Fynn, aka the mum from 🇸🇬 who loves creating fun learning activities with trash. 😆 That is still a fact after 6 years, but I found a bigger love to design learning activities that are fun for children and easy for busy parents. Here are 5 more fun facts about me:
🔴 I worked as a professional makeup artist for 3 years, and I did makeup for weddings, theatre shows and fashion shows for brands like Marc Jacobs, Hermès, D&G. 
🟠 I taught Chemistry in an IB college in Sweden for a year. And in the afternoon after school, I worked part time at a bridal studio or walked around the town taking photos. Ahh, all the fun things I did before kids came along. 😊
🟡 The longest I stayed at a place was 2.5years. Since I married my husband in 2009, we moved 8 times in 12 years. I think we are finally settled down and hopefully we will break the 2.5years record at our current place. 
🟢 I LOVE fantasy stories/ movies with another world, superheros, magic or mythical creatures  like Harry Potter, Avengers, Fantastic Beasts, How to Train Your Dragon. I secretly wish I have a Night Fury as my pet. 
🔵 I really dread folding and ironing clothes and I can’t decide which one I dread more. Send me a folding and ironing machine anyone? 😆
.
.
I hope you enjoyed reading these fun facts! Come say hi in the comments and share a fun fact about yourself with me! ❤️

And definitely save this post and try this fun activity with your children! ❤️

Fly to the Moon Counting Toy🚀
If I have to choose just one favorite activity from our Space Theme Discovery Pack, it must be this one! My 8yo loves this one so much that he went on to make his own space scene obstacle courses and challenge his younger sisters and me!

Love this idea too? Save this post and try this activity one day! This printable is part of our Space Theme Discovery Pack inside #thehappylearnersclub ⭐️
